        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Philada. 5 <hi rend="sup">th</hi> mo. 17 <hi rend="sup">Th</hi> 1869<lb/>
            Rev. S. Morais.<lb/>
            Dear Sir<lb/>
                For the purpose<lb/> of investigation&#44; into matters pertaining<lb/> to the Jewish faith I desire a copy<lb/> of the &#34;Talmud&#34; and would be<lb/> happy to secure from you&#44; a list of<lb/> such Jewish publications&#44; as would<lb/> in your estimation assist me in<lb/> the matter.  If not <sic>tresspassing</sic> on<lb/> your valuable time.  Will you be kind<lb/> enough to let me hear from you.<lb/>  I am not a member of any sect<lb/>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            or wedded to any creed but desire<lb/> by a thorough investigation with<lb/> the light that is given me into all<lb/> matters within my reach to arrive<lb/> at the right&#44; believing that the<lb/> foundation of Faith should be<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; for our Creator and charity<lb/> toward all men<lb/>
            Respectfully Yours<lb/>
            Chas. McShami<lb/>
                32 <hi rend="sup">nd</hi> &#38; Chestnut<lb/>
            West Philada<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 Nth 5th<lb/>
                Philada<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
